this is a database driver !
most popular driver for connecting python to postgreSQL

what it does ?

it acts as a bridge 

it lets your python talk to your postgresql database 

sends commands , it sends your SQL queries from python to the database 

it brings back data: it gets the results back and turns them into python format 

Python cannot talk to PostgreSQL on its own. It needs this driver to understand how to connect and share information.

pip install psycopg[binary] sqlalchemy python-dotenv